Name: Description
Asthma Emergency Department Visits:
Number of asthma emergency department (ED) visits among NYC resident children by age groups (0 to 4, 5 to 17 and 0 to 17).
Rate of asthma emergency department (ED) visits per 10,000 children in specific age groups (0 to 4, 5 to 17 and 0 to 17).

Name: Source Notes
Asthma Emergency Department Visits: New York State Statewide Planning and Research Cooperative System (SPARCS) Deidentified Hospital Discharge Data, retrieved from New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene NYC Tracking Program: Environment and Health Data Portal. [Asthma Emergency Department Visits; 2005-2016]. http://a816-dohbesp.nyc.gov/IndicatorPublic/

Name: Notes
Asthma Emergency Department Visits:
Rates are calculated by using number of asthma-related emergency department (ED) visits among NYC resident children for particular age group, divided by the population of children for the same age group, expressed as cases per 10,000 resident children for the respective age group (i.e. asthma-related emergency department (ED) visits among NYC resident children ages 0 to 4, divided by the population of children ages 0 to 4, expressed as cases per 10,000 population ages 0 to 4).

UHFs with the value of 0 represent data suppressed by DOHMH due to small sample size or insufficient data.
